  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2005-02-17",
    "date": "2005-03-10T19:50:12Z",
    "text": "Citizen Involvement in Campaigns Act of 2005 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow: (1) a $200 tax credit ($400 for joint returns) for contributions to a candidate for Federal elective public office or to the national committee of a national political party; and (2) a tax deduction (available to taxpayers who do not itemize deductions) for such political contributions up to $600 ($1,200 for joint returns)."
  },
